This paper discusses the AIM 2019 challenge on real world super-resolution, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The challenge involves training models to super-resolve images, which is a task that can be approached using machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of artificial image degradations, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
